# Line-ending rules. Without these, Git on Windows can rewrite the Unix
# `gradlew` script with CRLF endings, which makes it fail to run on Linux CI
# ("bad interpreter"). Pin the shell script to LF and the batch script to CRLF.
*           text=auto
gradlew     text eol=lf
*.sh        text eol=lf
*.bat       text eol=crlf
*.jar       binary
*.png       binary
